textAfterTable: Old slow stacking Since patch 5.13 only slow with the highest value is affecting. All additional slows are ignored. Prior to patch 5.13 slow stacked: Slowing effects followed particular rules when stacking: If a champion was affected by multiple slows, the strongest one would be fully applied, while the others were applied sequentially with 65% reduced effectiveness down to 35% of its original strength. Slow effects derived from items with the same name or named item effect did NOT stack, even when coming from different champions. Only the strongest item slow was applied at any moment.
